The manifold of undisplaced Gaussian states we can prepare is intuitively understood by plotting the results from Fig. 2d, e in the phase space of the prepared squeezing level and angle, as it is shown in Fig. 3 (see Supplementary Note 4 and Supplementary Fig. 4 for details). The purity \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
